OL,3,CNew test to prevent newborn babies
OL,4,Cgoing deaf to be trialled across the UK
OL,6,FThe test uses a cheek swab to identify
OL,7,Fin 26 minutes whether a critically ill
OL,8,Fbaby admitted to intensive care has a
OL,9,Fgene change that causes permanent
OL,10,Fhearing loss when given gentamicin.
OL,12,FWhile gentamicin is used to safely
OL,13,Ftreat approximately 100,000 babies a
OL,14,Fyear, one in 500 babies carry this
OL,15,Fgenetic variant that can result in
OL,16,Fdeafness.
OL,18,FBabies found to have the variant can
OL,19,Fbe given an alternative antibiotic.
